  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A pre-loaded auto-injector blending battlefield analgesics with off-label muscle accelerators. Issued unofficially to private military contractors; recovered routinely from the dead. The label warns of cardiac risk in fine print no one reads.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 minute you gain a +1d4 bonus to weapon attack rolls and damage rolls (single die rolled at apply, applied throughout the duration).</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Combat Cocktail (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Combat Cocktail.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned and have disadvantage on Charisma saving throws (you can't shake the post-firefight jitter).</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 4.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(4 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 2) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Syringe.</em></p>"
    },
